SIMPLE: oscillation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oscillation
<hw>Os`cil*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>oscillatio</ets> a swinging.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of oscillating; a swinging or moving
backward and forward, like a pendulum; vibration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fluctuation; variation; change back and
forth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His mind oscillated, undoubtedly; but the extreme points of the
<qex>oscillation</qex> were not very remote.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Axis of oscillation</b></col>, <col><b>Center of
oscillation</b></col></mcol>. <cd>See under <er>Axis</er>, and
<er>Center</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oscillative</ent>⟦br⟧
